result.name: Hattendo

reviews.text:
Food quality is ok, price on the pricy side for what it is. Service and seating are quite basic. 
The soufflé pancake is a bit cold to my liking, doesn’t have the freshly baked feel despite we waited for 30 mins which was supposed to be the baking time.
Smelly beef. Beef served was entirely different from photo from menu too. Told the waitress about it and she say the chef doesn't care. Worst meal of my entire trip in hong kong.

Speed: very slow (over 20 mins)
Taste: just average
Price: just fair for TST district ~$100/person)
many seats were taken by tourist and no staff cleaning up ( don't see any signs for self service or return trays, so very messy around the shop)
The beef udon is over cooked (like eating gums)
A Japanese light meal restaurant, serving some sets, drinks, dessert and bread, the price was a bit expensive, taste fair only.

We were there for a quick ice cream, iced coffee and a hot flat white. To our surprise, all 3 items are extremely delightful.  The seating area is self served and people actually buy cheesecake from the Factory beside to enjoy with the coffee.  Great idea!

reviews.text: 附設用餐區，午餐套餐不貴還有送招牌麵包，以價錢來說划算，但麵包真的不知好吃在哪裡…
在地面入口大堂容易找到。曾試過在東京的店鋪感覺味道是一樣的美味。環境開揚，卡位舒適。今天星期日十二時到達都沒有太多人。可能熱潮過後就冇新鮮感了。所以要來食就要快啦。這樣的客量真不看可以維持多久。

Food quality is ok, price on the pricy side for what it is. Service and seating are quite basic. 
The soufflé pancake is a bit cold to my liking, doesn’t have the freshly baked feel despite we waited for 30 mins which was supposed to be the baking time.
吉士Bun太。。。。好味，一定要試😋
